The Chairman/Chief Executive Officer of the National Hajj Commission of Nigeria (NAHCON), Alhaji Zikrullah Kunle Hassan, yesterday appealed to stakeholders in the aviation sector to ensure intending pilgrims enjoy hitch-free flights to Kingdom Saudi Arabia. Hassan said this during a visit to the Director-General of Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority (NCAA), Capt. Musa Nuhu, Managing Director of Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN), Capt. Rabiu Hamisu Yadudu; Director-General of Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NIMET), Prof Mansur Matazu; Director Port Health, and other relevant agencies involved in Hajj operations. According to him, there is need to have a smooth, safe and efficient airlift of pilgrims to the Saudi Arabia. He urged them to ensure all airports, aircraft, and airspaces were ready before the inaugural flight.   Commercial motorcyclists sue Lagos over restriction     Nigeria committed to clean energy sources, says Buhari     SON, Dangote advises block moulders, artisans on standard   The NAHCON boss also spoke on the need for pilgrims to meet the basic health requirements for the travelling which include PCR test, Yellow card issuance, and COVID-19 vaccines before departure to avoid problems and avert delays. He thanked the management of the NCAA and other organisations that were part of the airline-screening exercise for their wonderful job. Responding, Capt. Nuhu said all aircraft will be inspected accordingly to ensure they are airworthy before they are allowed into Nigeriaâ€™s airspace to commence the Hajj airlift. This, he said, cannot be compromised. Prof Matazu assured that the pre-Hajj inspection will be done, along with close monitoring and observation of the weather before the commencement of each flight.